@@ -126,6 +126,27 @@ Return ``schedule.CancelJob`` from a job to remove it from the scheduler.
         time.sleep(1)
 
 
+Run a job a limited number of times
+~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
+
+Use ``Job.max_runs(n)`` to remove a job from the scheduler after its function
+has run ``n`` times.
+
+.. code-block:: python
+
+    import schedule
+    import time
+
+    def job():
+        print("I'm working...")
+
+    schedule.every().minute.max_runs(3).do(job)
+
+    while True:
+        schedule.run_pending()
+        time.sleep(1)
+
+
 Get all jobs
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~
 To retrieve all jobs from the scheduler, use ``schedule.get_jobs()``
